{"batchId":"","ingestionId":"","fundingBodyId":89477598,"homePage":"https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/8602.html","status":"ACTIVE","preferredName":[{"language":"en","value":"Institute of Neurosciences, Mental Health and Addiction"},{"language":"fr","value":"Institut des neurosciences, de la santé mentale et des toxicomanies"}],"acronym":[{"language":"en","value":"INMHA"},{"language":"fr","value":"INSMT"}],"abbrevName":[{"language":"en","value":"NOTFOUND"},{"language":"fr","value":"NOTFOUND"}],"alternateName":[{"language":"en","value":"NOTFOUND"},{"language":"fr","value":"NOTFOUND"}],"financeType":"GOV","activityType":"GOVFED","country":"CAN","state":"Alberta","identifier":[{"type":"CROSSREFID","value":"NOTFOUND"}],"description":[{"abstract":{"language":"en","value":"As the federal agency responsible for investing in health research, the Canadian Institutes of Health Research (CIHR) seeks to create new knowledge and translate it into improved health outcomes for Canadians. The Institute of Neurosciences, Mental Health and Addiction (INMHA), one of thirteen CIHR Institutes, contributes to this mandate by supporting research, knowledge exchange and translation on the function and disorders of the brain, spinal cord, sensory systems and mind.INSMT supports research to improve knowledge about the brain in the areas of mental health, neurological health, vision, hearing and cognitive functioning. Our goal is to reduce the incidence of brain diseases through prevention strategies, screening, diagnosis, treatment, support systems and palliative care. We will advance our understanding of human thought and emotion, behaviour, sensory perception (sight, hearing, touch, taste, smell), learning and memory.Adequately supported and ethically responsible discovery science that is distinguished by excellence and innovation, encompassing all aspects of nervous system and mental health research and clinical application, resulting in quality health care and respecting the diversity of culture and values of all Canadians"},"source":"https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/8579.html"},{"abstract":{"language":"fr","value":"En tant qu’organisme fédéral chargé d’investir dans la recherche en santé, les Instituts de recherche en santé du Canada (IRSC) veulent créer de nouvelles connaissances et les mettre en application pour améliorer la santé de la population canadienne. L’Institut des neurosciences, de la santé mentale et des toxicomanies (INSMT), l’un des treize instituts des IRSC, contribue à la réalisation de ce mandat en appuyant la recherche ainsi que l’échange et l’application des connaissances sur le fonctionnement et les troubles du cerveau, de la moelle épinière, des systèmes sensoriels et de l’esprit.L’INSMT appuie la recherche visant à améliorer les connaissances relatives au cerveau, dans les domaines de la santé mentale, de la santé neurologique, de la vision, de l’ouïe et du fonctionnement cognitif. Notre objectif est de réduire l’incidence des maladies du cerveau par des stratégies de prévention, le dépistage, le diagnostic, le traitement, les systèmes de soutien et les soins palliatifs. Nous ferons progresser notre compréhension de la pensée humaine et des émotions, du comportement, de la perception sensorielle (vue, ouïe, toucher, goût, odorat), de l’apprentissage et de la mémoire.Une science de la découverte au soutien adéquat et éthiquement responsable qui se distingue par son excellence et son caractère novateur, qui englobe tous les aspects de la recherche sur le système nerveux et la santé mentale ainsi que l’application clinique, lesquelles se traduisent par des soins de santé de qualité et respectent la diversité de la culture et des valeurs de l’ensemble de la population canadienne."},"source":"https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/f/8579.html"}],"awardSuccessRate":{"percentage":0,"description":[{"abstract":{"language":"en","value":"NOTFOUND"},"source":""},{"abstract":{"language":"fr","value":"NOTFOUND"},"source":""}]},"establishment":{"establishmentYear":0,"country":"CAN","description":[{"abstract":{"language":"en","value":"NOTFOUND"},"source":""},{"abstract":{"language":"fr","value":"NOTFOUND"},"source":""}]},"fundingPolicy":[{"abstract":{"language":"en","value":"CIHR strategic research initiatives are funded through Institute strategic initiative budgets and/or dedicated funding from government and external partners. Funding for these initiatives is not sourced from CIHR’s Project Grant competition.The Institute of Neurosciences, Mental Health and Addiction (INMHA) funds health research in order to develop and support a well-trained base of investigators with the skills and expertise needed to design and conduct innovative and diverse research and knowledge translation activities aimed at improving health."},"source":"https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/46897.html"},{"abstract":{"language":"fr","value":"Les initiatives de recherche stratégique des IRSC sont financées par les budgets stratégiques des instituts ou par des fonds du gouvernement et de partenaires externes destinés à cette fin. Les fonds ne proviennent pas du concours de subventions Projet des IRSC.L'Institut des neurosciences, de la santé mentale et des toxicomanies (INSMT) finance la recherche en santé en vue de constituer et de financer un bassin de chercheurs bien formés possédant les aptitudes et l'expertise nécessaires à l'élaboration et à la réalisation d'activités de recherche et d'application des connaissances à la fois novatrices et variées qui visent à améliorer la santé."},"source":"https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/f/46897.html"}],"contactInformation":{"hasPostalAddress":{"addressCountry":"CAN","addressRegion":"NOTFOUND","addressLocality":"Calgary","addressPostalCode":"T2N 4N1","postOfficeBoxNumber":"NOTFOUND","streetAddress":"3330 Hospital Drive NW, Heritage Medical Research Building, Room 172"}},"relation":{"partOf":[0],"hasPart":[0],"affiliatedWith":[0],"renamedAs":[0],"continuationOf":[0],"mergedWith":[0],"incorporatedInto":[0],"mergerOf":[0],"incorporates":[0